metadata.name: Paper Cut
metadata.description:
"Paper Cut" is a more colorful representation of my habit of folding all sorts of paper when I am in deep thought about things that worry me. I am quite the overthinker, and struggle to get my words out. Table napkins at diners/cafes, receipts laying around, notebooks...they're all victims to my anxiety. Triangles are my favorite thing to fold apparently. 

Honestly this piece came out much brighter than I had planned... I must have a habit of using bright colors to cover the deeper meaning behind my pieces. 
I wanted the stickers on her hand to cover paper cuts. They symbolize false happiness that covers the pain deep down. I hope you enjoy this piece :)

Collector will receive a derivative commission ticket. 
All bidders will receive a thank you stamp. <3 
Thank you everyone. 

Dimensions: 3000 x 4000 px
300 DPI
